Chunk 3 (final!) — Rate limiting 🚦

The why, with a real danger:

Your app has a "Send me a code" button (the OTP one). What stops someone from clicking it 10,000 times in a minute?

Right now: nothing. 😬 That means:
- 10,000 emails fired off
- Your Gmail gets flagged/banned for spam
- Your server drowns

Rate limiting = a cap on how often someone can hit a button.

Like: "You can only request a code 3 times per hour. After that, wait."

Without limit:  click click click click click ×10000  →  disaster
With limit:     click click click 🛑 "slow down, try later"

It's a bouncer on your endpoints — lets a reasonable number through, blocks the spammers.

That's the why. Ready to add the bouncer? (Install + a couple of decorator lines.)

